FBIS4-18920 "drweu070_h_94008" FBIS-WEU-94-070 Daily Report 11 Apr 1994 GERMANY Court Passes Sentence in Maison de France Trial Court Passes Sentence in Maison de France Trial AU1104185794 Mainz ZDF Television Network in German 1700 GMT 11 Apr 94 AU1104185794 Mainz ZDF Television Network German BFN [Text] A sentence has been handed down in the trial involving the terrorist attack on the Maison de France [in August 1983] in Berlin. Former Stasi officer Vogt was sentenced to four years in prison, but was released for the time being [until the sentence becomes nonappealable]. The Berlin Court considered it proven that the 51-year-old man had passed the explosives for the attack on to terrorist Weinrich. With this, the Stasi had provided active support for the terrorist attack.
